# i18nprune

## Source of truth
- **Local-only WIP:** `maintainer/temp/` — temporary plans and scratch (**gitignored**; not in clone history; read it on disk only if the user keeps notes there).
- Active plans: `maintainer/phases/extractor.md`. Read first.
- Shipped receipts: `maintainer/phases/shipped-slices.md`.
- Hub: `maintainer/phases/V1-RELEASE.md`. Active sprint focus: `maintainer/phases/active-phase.md`.
- Contributor/agent subsystem maps (not user docs): `maintainer/systems/README.md`.
- Agent coding guides: `maintainer/agents/README.md`. **Architecture:** `maintainer/agents/architecture.md`. **Git hygiene:** `maintainer/agents/git.md`. **JSDoc:** `maintainer/agents/jsdoc.md` (when/where/how). Task checklist: `maintainer/phases/jsdoc.md`.

## Build / test gate
- Required before commit: `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm test`.
- Refactor PRs: parity snapshot tests under `tests/parity/` must pass.

## Behavior parity (refactors)
- `--json` envelope, stripped human stderr output, exit codes, and issue codes on the sample fixture must not change byte-for-byte during a refactor.
- Issue codes are stable API: never rename existing codes (e.g. `english_identical_leaves`) even when display copy changes.

## Folder & type conventions
- Public types live in `packages/core/src/types/<domain>/` with an `index.ts` barrel.
- CLI never re-exports core types via shim files.
- Op orchestration entries: `packages/core/src/<op>/run.ts`, re-exported from `<op>/index.ts`.

## Core purity
- No `console.*` calls in `packages/core/src/**`.
- No `process.*` access in core except via a passed-in `env` parameter.
- File IO in core only via passed-in host adapters (or a core-side adapters re-export).

## Pre-v1
- No backwards-compat constraints on internal APIs.
- User-facing surfaces (CLI argv, `--json` envelope, log lines, exit codes, issue codes) are NOT internal — those are frozen by the parity rule above.

## Discipline
- One slice per PR. Match the slice scope from the active plan doc.
- Decisions in the plan docs are LOCKED unless surfaced first with file:line evidence.
- If a doc is ambiguous, ASK. Do not guess.
- Maintainer-only: `maintainer/**` is not mirrored to user-facing docs (`apps/docs/`); keep that boundary.
- **`docs/**` (VitePress):** public, user-facing copy. Do not embed maintainer phase/session plans, sprint status, or `maintainer/` cross-links unless unavoidable; use plain language and `docs/` links. Contributor depth belongs in `maintainer/systems/` and `maintainer/phases/` (see `maintainer/agents/README.md` § Docs site).
